President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing National Doctors Day on March 30, 2020. In the proclamation, he expresses gratitude for the dedication and hard work of doctors and other medical professionals in combating the coronavirus pandemic. He acknowledges their efforts in treating patients, finding cures, and providing care with dignity and empathy. President Trump praises their work in hospitals, research facilities, and in reassuring and informing the American people. He believes that the United States is well-prepared to fight the pandemic due to the talent and innovation of its medical professionals. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe National Doctors Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.